title: Finding Intercepts of a Parabola
body: The quadratic equation $$h=16t^2+vt+h$$ models the height of a volleyball hit straight upwards with initial velocity $$176$$ feet per second from a height of $$4$$ feet. $$h$$ is the hiehgt, $$t$$ is the time, and v is the initial velocity.
lesson: 10.5 Graphing Quadratic Equations in Two Variables
